# OvertheWire-Bandit-Levels
Tips for OTW Bandit challenges
Before reading the solution i recommend you to check the man of nmap and ncat

-------------------------LEVEL16--------------------------
#First you must use nmap to scan the localhost ports from 31000 to 32000
nmap -A localhost -p 31000-32000

#Then use the command ncat to submit the current password to get the new one
ncat --ssl localhost "PORT"

#Finally connect to bandit17 from your own machine
ssh -i "KEY WITH THE PASSWORD" bandit17@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220

-------------------------LEVEL 17-------------------------
#For this level you have to use the command "diff"
diff passwords.new passwords.old
#The output "<" belongs to the first input file and ">" to the last one (you have to choose the password from passwords.new)

